rComments: The WORST prof ever. He is so disorganized, won't reply to emails, expects you to know everything, and is a terrible lecturer. He asks for feedback and then doesn't implement it.

Dr. Gomes is a kind man. Students always come in with a bad attitude and never participate when he asks question, so he gets kinda annoyed. He is willing to help people and make exceptions on projects if you just ask him. He is always asking for feedback and how to improve. Ummmmmm I really dont know what to say lol he's very rude, you walk out of class more confused than ever! Material wise its an easy class but man oh man were his lectures painful to attend. His slides were fill in the blank but yet hardly anyone showed up to class

literally the worst prof. just avoid him. he doesnt teach, he doesnt know the content himself

He asked his students multiple times what he could do to be better - added extra questions on to his teacher evaluation and asked a couple of times in class. Cut him some slack, if you need something ask instead of whining about it and being rude to him. It's not a hard class, just read the textbook or the slides and you will be fine.

rComments: Definitely don't need to show up to class or do any of the readings. All the info that students were tested on can be found on the slides, granted the slides were text-heavy and LONG. His lectures are dreadful since he reads them word for word with a monotone voice. Provides practice questions which are IDENTICAL to the ones on the exams except he tends to give incorrect answers to the questions. Slideshows are over detail and he focuses on small details rather the big concept. The most unorganized person I've ever met!
